---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Accessibility"
  description="Accessibility statement for Chiltern Computers - Our commitment to making our services accessible to everyone."
>
  <div class="section-bg-3" style="padding: 120px 20px 80px; min-height: 100vh;">
    <div class="container">
      
      <!-- Page Header -->
      <div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 60px;">
        <h1 class="space-font galaxy-text cosmic-glow" style="font-size: clamp(32px, 6vw, 48px); margin-bottom: 16px;">
          Accessibility
        </h1>
        <div style="height: 3px; width: 120px; background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--solar-orange), var(--mars-red)); margin: 0 auto 20px; border-radius: 2px;"></div>
        <p class="alien-font" style="color: var(--comet-silver); font-size: 16px; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto;">
          We‚Äôre dedicated to making our services and website accessible to everyone.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Accessibility Content -->
      <div class="cosmic-card" style="padding: 40px; max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
        
        <div class="accessibility-section">
          <h2 class="space-font" style="color: var(--solar-orange); font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Our Commitment</h2>
          <p class="alien-font" style="color: var(--starlight-white); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 20px;">
            Chiltern Computers is committed to digital accessibility. We work hard to improve the experience for all users and follow recognised accessibility standards.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="accessibility-section">
          <h4 class="space-font" style="color: var(--solar-orange); font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Website Accessibility</h4>
          <p class="alien-font" style="color: var(--starlight-white); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 12px;">
            Our website is built to be easy to use and accessible to everyone. We aim to meet WCAG 2.1 AA standards by including:
          </p>
          <ul class="alien-font" style="color: var(--starlight-white); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 20px; padding-left: 20px;">
            <li>Simple navigation and clear layout</li>
            <li>Descriptive text for links and images</li>
            <li>Strong colour contrast for readability</li>
            <li>Support for keyboard navigation</li>
            <li>Mobile-friendly and responsive design</li>
            <li>Compatibility with screen readers</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="accessibility-section">
          <h3 class="space-font" style="color: var(--solar-orange); font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Physical Accessibility</h3>
          <p class="alien-font" style="color: var(--starlight-white); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 12px;">
            At our Harold Hill location, we aim to make in-person services as accessible as possible:
          </p>
          <ul class="alien-font" style="color: var(--starlight-white); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 20px; padding-left: 20px;">
            <li>Ground floor entry</li>
            <li>Collection and delivery services</li>
            <li>Flexible appointment times</li>
            <li>Clear and patient communication</li>
            <li>Support by phone, email, or in person</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="accessibility-section">
          <h3 class="space-font" style="color: var(--solar-orange); font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Assistive Technology Support</h3>
          <p class="alien-font" style="color: var(--starlight-white); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 20px;">
            We‚Äôre familiar with many assistive tools and can advise on setting up computers to work well with screen readers, voice software, and other technology.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="accessibility-section">
          <h3 class="space-font" style="color: var(--solar-orange); font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Communication Preferences</h3>
          <p class="alien-font" style="color: var(--starlight-white); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 12px;">
            We offer several ways to get help or support:
          </p>
          <ul class="alien-font" style="color: var(--starlight-white); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 20px; padding-left: 20px;">
            <li>Phone support with patient guidance</li>
            <li>Email for detailed help and instructions</li>
            <li>Face-to-face meetings with visual help</li>
            <li>Written quotes and service details</li>
            <li>Support for family or carers joining the discussion</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="accessibility-section">
          <h3 class="space-font" style="color: var(--solar-orange); font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Ongoing Improvements</h3>
          <p class="alien-font" style="color: var(--starlight-white); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 20px;">
            We review our website and services regularly to improve them. We welcome your feedback and ideas on how we can do better.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="accessibility-section">
          <h3 class="space-font" style="color: var(--solar-orange); font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Browser and Assistive Technology Compatibility</h3>
          <p class="alien-font" style="color: var(--starlight-white); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 12px;">
            Our website works well with:
          </p>
          <ul class="alien-font" style="color: var(--starlight-white); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 20px; padding-left: 20px;">
            <li>Popular browsers like Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge</li>
            <li>Screen readers such as JAWS, NVDA, and VoiceOver</li>
            <li>Voice control software</li>
            <li>Keyboard-only browsing</li>
            <li>Zoom up to 200%</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="accessibility-section">
          <h3 class="space-font" style="color: var(--solar-orange); font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Feedback and Support</h3>
          <p class="alien-font" style="color: var(--starlight-white); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 20px;">
            If you find any accessibility issues or have ideas to improve, please let us know. We‚Äôre here to help and value your input.
          </p>
          <div style="background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.1); border: 1px solid var(--solar-orange); border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; margin-top: 12px;">
